And
the
third
angel
followed
them,
saying
with
a
loud
voice,
If
any
man
worship
the
beast
and
his
image,
and
receive
his
mark
in
his
forehead,
or
in
his
hand,
The
same
shall
drink
of
the
wine
of
the
wrath
of
God,
which
is
poured
out
without
mixture
into
the
cup
of
his
indignation;
and
he
shall
be
tor-
mented
with
fire
and
brimstone
in
the

the

angels,
and
in
the

Lamb:
And

of

ascendeth
up
forever

ever:
and

nor
night,
who
worship
the
beast
and
his
image,
and
whosoever
receiv-
eth

mark

Here

the
patience
of
the
saints:
here
are
they
that
keep
the
com-
mandments
of
God,
and
the
faith
of
Jesus.
And
I

a

Write,
Blessed

the
dead
which
die
in
the
Lord

henceforth:
Yea,

Spirit,
that

rest

and

And

Oh
that
men
would
praise
the
Lord
for
his
goodness,
and
for
his
won-
derful
works
to
the
children
of
men!
And
let
them
sacrifice
the
sac-
rifkes
of
thanksgiving,
and
de-
clare
his
works
with
rejoicing.
They
that
go
down
to
the
sea
in
ships,
that
do
business
in
great
waters;
these
see
the
works
of
the
Lord,
and
his
wonders
in
the
deep.
For
he

and
raiseth
the
stormy

which

up
the
waves
thereof.
They
mount
up
to
the
heaven,
they
go
down
again
to

depths:
their
soul
is
melted
because
of
trouble.
They
reel
to
and
fro,
and
stagger
like
a
drunken
man,
and
are
at
their
wit's
end.
Then
they
cry
unto
the
Lord
in
their

and
he
bringeth
them
out
of
their
distresses.
He
maketh
the
storm
a
calm,
so
that
the
waves
thereof
are
still.
Then
are
they
glad
because
they
be
quiet;
so
he
bringeth
them
unto
their
desired
haven.
Oh
that
men
would
praise
the
Lord
for
his
goodness,
and
for
his
wonderful
works
to
the
chil-
dren
of
men!
Let

exalt
him
also
in
the
con-
gregation
of
the
people,
and

him
in
the
assembly
of
the
elders.
He
turneth
rivers
into
a

ness,
and
the
watersprings
into
dry
ground;
a
fruitful
land
into
barrenness,
for
the
wickedness
of
them
that
dwell
therein.
He
turneth
the
wilderness
into
a
standing
water,
and
dry
ground
into
wa
tersprings.
And
there

to
